ep/21/neo-fascist-greek-party-election-golden-dawn-third-place}}</ref><br />[[Social conservatism]]<ref>{{cite book|page=196|title=Crisis, Movement, Strategy: The Greek Experience|publisher=BRILL|first=Panagiotis|last=Sotiris|year=2018}}</ref><br />[[National conservatism]]<ref>{{cite book|page=47|title=Aligning Geopolitics, Humanitarian Action and Geography in Times of Conflict|first=Gerry|last=O'Reilly|year=2019|publisher=Springer}}</ref><br />[[Economic nationalism]]<ref>{{cite journal|title=Thirties Throwbacks: Explaining the Electoral Breakthroughs of Jobbik and Golden Dawn|year=2014|publisher=[[Tufts University]]|first=William|last=Rose|url=http://as.tufts.edu/politicalscience/sites/all/themes/asbase/assets/documents/research/thirtiesThrowbacks.pdf}}</ref><br />[[Euroscepticism|Hard Euroscepticism]]<ref name=\"euroscrepticism5\">[https://eu.boell.org/sites/default/files/greek_right_wing_populist_parties_and_euroscepticism.pdf Antonis Galanopoulos: Greek right-wing populist parties and Euroscepticism](PDF), p.2 \"Golden Dawn is also Eurosceptical and it is opposing Greece's participation in the European Union and the Eurozone\"</ref><ref name=\"euroscrepticism6\">[http://www.france24.com/en/20140527-europe-pictures-european-parliament-eurosceptic-parties-fn-ukip France24: A look at the European Parliament's eurosceptic parties], Golden Dawn, Greece</ref><ref name=\"euroscrepticism7\">[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/sep/16/greek-election-2015-golden-dawn-austerity The Guardian: Greek election 2015: Golden Dawn rises on austerity-driven despair], \"In successive opinion surveys, the virulently [...] anti-EU party has emerged as Greece's third-biggest political force\"</ref><ref name=\"euroscrepticism8\">[http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/783e39b4-e4af-11e3-9b2b-00144feabdc0.html#slide0 Financial Times: Anti-EU parties celebrate election success], 26 May 2014</ref><br />[[Right-wing populism]]<ref>{{cite journal|first=Mats|last=Ekstr\u00f6m|title=Right-wing populi